      "side": 1,
      "message": "Generally, I think it is good to let an object \"handle its own business\". Provide a layer of abstraction so that if the internals change, users of the object don\u0027t have to make code updates.\n\nIt seems like lines 36-57 could be within a Chassis::initializePowerSystemInputStatus() method instead? The System class probably doesn\u0027t need to know about these internal details of the Chassis class. Let the Chassis class define its own object path, create the ChassisPowerSystemInterface that it will own, handle the exception, etc.",
